Individual




Ellen R. Strahlman



Dr. Ellen R. Strahlman, MD, is Chief Medical Officer, EVP-Research & Development at Becton, Dickinson & Co. She is on the Board of Directors at Losonoco Ltd. and Syncona Partners LLP.
Dr. Strahlman was previously employed as Chief Medical Officer & Senior Vice President by GlaxoSmithKline Plc, Chief Medical Officer & Global Head-Research by Bausch & Lomb, Inc., a Principal by Merck & Co., Inc., a Principal by Novartis Corp., and Vice President-Worldwide Business Development by Pfizer Inc.
She received her undergraduate degree from Harvard University, a graduate degree from the Johns Hopkins Bloomberg School of Public Health, and a doctorate degree from The Johns Hopkins University School of Medicine.



