 IN MEMORIAM: D.A. HENDERSON1928 - 2016Home > About > School at a Glance > Health Advisory Board > Board Members > Ellen Strahlman  Ellen Strahlman, MD, MHSc Senior Vice President, Research & Development Chief Medical OfficerEllen Strahlman, MD, MHSc, is a senior executive with 23 years of international experience in the healthcare industry (biopharmaceuticals, medical devices, public health).  She is currently the Senior Vice President, Research & Development and Chief Medical Officer and for Becton, Dickinson and Company, a leading global medical technology company.Dr Strahlman reports to BD’s CEO, Vincent Forlenza, and has accountability for the Company’s Innovation System as well as R&D and Medical Affairs functions.  As an Officer of the Company, she serves on the CEO’s Management Committee, Worldwide Operating Committee, the BD Leadership Team, Corporate Business Development Team, Corporate Ethics Steering Team and CenterPoint Steering Team.   In her Management capacity, she Co-Chairs the company’s Innovation Council, Chairs the R&D Management Committee and the Medical Affairs Leadership Team and leads the newly established Office of Science, Medicine & Technology for BD.Dr. Strahlman joined BD in May 2013 from GlaxoSmithKline, plc, having served as the Senior Vice President and Chief Medical Officer (CMO) since 2008 and also working in the Office of the CEO as Senior Medical Advisor and Global Head of Neglected Tropical Diseases.  As GSK’s CMO, Dr. Strahlman had accountability for medical safety and patient matters for development programs and commercialized products in the Vaccines, Pharmaceutical and Consumer businesses, as well as organizational oversight for activities that included medical affairs, product development, clinical safety and pharmacovigilance, regulatory affairs, quality and compliance.   Known for her scientific and patient-centric leadership across the continuum of product ideation, development and commercialization, Dr. Strahlman has led teams developing pharmaceuticals, medical devices, generics and consumer products in nearly every therapeutic category since 1991.  She has served at the executive level in roles leading R&D, Medical Affairs, Scientific Affairs, and Business Development organizations. Her executive experience includes leadership roles at Merck, Bausch & Lomb, Novartis, Pfizer, and GSK; and she has also worked as a biotech CEO.Throughout her career, Ellen has, and continues to be, a passionate advocate for global heath and has worked to create business solutions designed to deliver equitable global access to high-quality healthcare services.  Well-versed in global health and international policy, Ellen has served as corporate liaison to the press, media and government agencies on a variety of medical and healthcare system related issues. As a spokesperson for the industry and biotechnology, she has addressed issues of public health and corporate social responsibility in the healthcare industrial sector. Ellen is a graduate of Harvard University (Biochemical Sciences) and obtained her medical degree from the Johns Hopkins School of Medicine.  She has medical qualifications in general surgery (Johns Hopkins) and ophthalmology (the Wilmer Institute, Johns Hopkins). Finally, Ellen earned her Masters Degree in Health Sciences from the Johns Hopkins Bloomberg School of Public Health as a Carnegie-Mellon Physician Public Health Fellow.Johns Hopkins Bloomberg School of Public Health 615 N. Wolfe Street, Baltimore, MD 21205Contact Us Directions & Maps Calendars Offices & Services Online Learning & Courses Careers Accreditation Web Policies FeedbackJHSPH Alumni my.jhsph.edu CoursePlus Student Information System (SIS) my.jhu.eduLike Us on Facebook Follow Us on Twitter Watch Videos on YouTube Follow us on Instagram Connect with LinkedInJohns Hopkins University





